OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FOutbreaks of
OL,6,Frain pushing northeast this evening,
OL,7,Fthe odd heavier burst in the west.
OL,8,FRemaining cloudy overnight with
OL,9,Foutbreaks of rain and much milder than
OL,10,Fof late.
OL,11,
OL,12,CSunday:FA cloudy start with outbreaks
OL,13,Fof rain. It will turn more showery
OL,14,Fduring the day with some brighter
OL,15,Fspells. The showers could be heavy,
OL,16,Fperhaps the odd rumble of thunder.
OL,17,
OL,18,COutlook for Monday to Wednesday:FMainly
OL,19,Fdry and bright on Monday with early
OL,20,Fshowers dying out. Rain or showers on
OL,21,FTuesday and Wednesday, heavy at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
